## \f1\u-10179?\u-8986?\f0  APK Hosting Strategy\par
\par
APK files will NOT be uploaded directly to Netlify. Instead, we use external hosting:\par
\par
### For APKs under 100MB:\par
1. **GitHub Repository** - Upload directly to your repo\par
   - Free and reliable\par
   - Simple to manage\par
   - Direct download links\par
   - File limit: 100MB per file\par
\par
### For APKs over 100MB (if needed in future):\par
1. **GitHub Releases** (Recommended)\par
   - File limit: 2GB per file\par
   - Professional approach\par
   - Version tracking\par
   - Direct download links\par
\par
2. **Google Drive** (Alternative)\par
   - Unlimited size (within your Drive space)\par
   - Generate direct download links\par
   - Easy to update\par
\par
3. **Dropbox** (Alternative)\par
   - Similar to Google Drive\par
   - Direct link sharing\par
\par
### How it Works:\par
- Your website (hosted on Netlify) contains only HTML/CSS/JS/images\par
- Download buttons link to external APK locations\par
- When users click download, they get the APK from GitHub/Drive\par
- This keeps your website fast and within Netlify's free limits\par
\par
**Recommended Setup:**\par
- APKs under 100MB \f3\u8594?\f0  GitHub repository `/apks` folder\par
- APKs over 100MB \f3\u8594?\f0  GitHub Releases or Google Drive\par
- Website always stays lightweight on Netlify\par
\par
